commentPreTextItems.html: The first of five one-day internationals between Pakistan and West Indies at Rawalpindi has been abandoned due to heavy rain. Umpires Daryl Harper and Aleem Dar called off the match after three days of torrential downpours left the ground waterlogged. Pakistan Cricket Board spokesman Naushad Ali said. "They have called off the match due to wet conditions of the ground and square." More
